'''{{lang|nl|Vereniging zonder winstoogmerk}}''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]], abbreviated '''''vzw''''') or '''{{lang|fr|Association sans but lucratif}}''' ([[French language|French]], abbreviated '''''asbl''''') or '''{{lang|de|Vereinigung ohne Gewinnerzielungsabsicht}}''' ([[German language|German]], abbreviated '''''VoG''''') is the legal term for a '[[Non-profit organization|not-for-profit association]]' in [[Belgium]]; the French term also applies in [[Luxembourg]] and the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. For international organisations, the equivalent is [[ivzw]] or [[aisbl]]. It is a formal designation under [[Belgium|Belgian]] and [[Luxembourg]] law, and organisations are entered in a register and allocated numeric identifiers.

'''Internationale vereniging zonder winstoogmerk''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]], often abbreviated '''IVZW''') or '''Association internationale sans but lucratif''' ([[French language|French]]; often abbreviated '''AISBL''') or '''Internationale Vereinigung ohne Gewinnerzielungsabsicht''' ([[German language|German]]; often abbreviated '''IVoG''') is the legal term used in Belgium for an internationally acting  [[Non-profit Organization|not-for-profit association]] based on Belgian law and located in [[Belgium]].<ref>[http://vsdc.be/Repository/Downloads/wet2meiversievooropsite.pdf For the legal text of the IVZV/IASBL, look at ''title III, Art. 46'' on page 38 (in Dutch & French)]</ref>

